docs/performance/ubuntu-x86-q8.md:82:Do not present negative host-access state in public repository files. Keep exact probe commands, raw stderr, return codes, host addresses, users, key paths, and working directories in private operator notes only. If remote validation is unavailable, use the public-safe unavailable-validation sentence.
docs/runtime/cross-lane-sync.md:9:- Report Ubuntu validation status as evidence status, not host-access status. If remote validation was not attempted for the current slice, say so; keep exact probe commands, raw stderr, return codes, host addresses, users, key paths, and working directories in private operator notes only.
